What is Apache HTTP Server?

Apache (Apache HTTP Server) is a web server software.
It is used to show websites on the internet.

ðŸ‘‰ When you open a website in your browser (like Chrome or Firefox), Apache sends the website files (HTML, CSS, images) to your browser.

âœ… Simple Meaning

Apache is a program that:

Stores website files

Handles user requests

Sends web pages to users

ðŸ–¥ Example

If you create a website and put it on a server:

Apache runs on that server

When someone types your website name

Apache shows your website to them

